Description: high-level concurrency / networking for asyncio + Trio (Avalan PPA pin)
 anyio is a high-level concurrency and networking framework that runs
 on top of either the asyncio or Trio event loops. This package is
 built for the Avalan PPA because mcp (Avalan's `server` extras)
 requires `anyio >= 4.5` while Noble ships 4.2.0. Pinned at 4.12.1 to
 mirror Debian sid; the same build also satisfies google-genai's
 stricter `>= 4.8.0` floor once that row is packaged.
